{
  "stem": "18654.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But this penny I was allowed to spend how I liked.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I could buy a banana with this, I could buy my milk at school with it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And apart-- apart from that, I only remember odd incidents.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because when the blitz started-- I remember the day war broke out, funnily enough, which was a Sunday-- I think.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I happened to be at the rabbi's house, I don't know why, maybe to-- for Hebrew lessons, possibly?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I came out of the house, and I saw what I thought were zeppelins in the sky.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was absolutely frightened out of my wits.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But they weren't zeppelins, they were barrage balloons.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All over the sky I saw these what I thought were zeppelins and later found out that they weren't, they were barrage balloons, which I don't know if you know what they are.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they were to protect, I think, against low flying aircraft.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When-- soon, when the blitz started-- the blitz of London, I mean-- I experienced part of that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But when it became really bad, my sister and I were evacuated to Ely in Cambridgeshire, where we were unfortunately separated.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was put in-- because nobody wanted two refugee kids or evacuees, I should say.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I was in one house, and she would be somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we used to only see each other at school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was there for, probably, I suppose a year and a half or something like that.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I became very ill there through neglect, and I was then sent to Cornwall, which is rather a long way from London.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I was put into a Jewish children's home in Cornwall, and I really never saw my sister.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
